         "maturity": "stable",
         "description": "<p style=\"font-size: 12.1599998474121px; line-height: 15.8079996109009px;\">This upload includes all input and control files used for the EVAC impact assessment. <\/p>\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 12.1599998474121px; line-height: 15.8079996109009px;\">The output files can be generated by executing the scenarios using the input data files (network and demand) and control files.<\/p>\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 12.1599998474121px; line-height: 15.8079996109009px;\">The Common_Inputs folder includes input files. <\/p>\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 12.1599998474121px; line-height: 15.8079996109009px;\">The Scenarios folder include control files for each EVAC scenario.<\/p>\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 12.1599998474121px; line-height: 15.8079996109009px;\">Documentation:<\/p>\r\n<ul style=\"font-size: 12.1599998474121px; line-height: 15.8079996109009px;\">\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #0066cc;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><a href=\"http://ntl.bts.gov/lib/48000/48500/48520/66C294FF.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Concept of Operations (R.E.S.C.U.M.E.)<\/a><\/span><\/span><\/li>\r\n<li><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><span style=\"color: #0066cc;\"><a href=\"http://ntl.bts.gov/lib/48000/48500/48519/32BFD176.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Report on Functional and Performance Requirements, and High-Level Data and Communication Needs<\/a><\/span><\/span><\/li>\r\n<li><a style=\"text-decoration: underline;\" href=\"http://ntl.bts.gov/lib/55000/55000/55045/R_E_S_C_U_M_E__EVAC_IAReport_FINAL_FHWA-JPO-15-204.pdf\">Emergency Communications for Evacuation (EVAC) in New Orleans Impact Assessment Report<\/a><\/li>\r\n<li><a style=\"text-decoration: underline;\" href=\"http://ntl.bts.gov/lib/55000/55300/55305/FHWA-JPO-14-137_v1.pdf\">Dynamic Mobility Application Policy Analysis: Policy and Institutional Issues for Response, Emergency Staging and Communications, Uniform Management, and Evacuation (R.E.S.C.U.M.E.)Dynamic Mobility Application Policy Analysis: Policy and Institutional Issues for Response, Emergency Staging and Communications, Uniform Management, and Evacuation (R.E.S.C.U.M.E.)<\/a><\/li>\r\n<\/ul>",
         "notes": "<p>- EVAC Impact Assessment Control Files and Input Files<\/p>\r\n<p> <\/p>\r\n<p>- What's New<\/p>\r\n<p>2015/04: The first release<\/p>\r\n<p> <\/p>\r\n<p>- System Requirements (third-party platforms / modules / etc with version numbers / dates)<\/p>\r\n<p>TRANSIMS v6 software is needed to use these files.<\/p>\r\n<p> <\/p>\r\n<p>- Features and changes (new features, defects corrected, caveats etc)<\/p>\r\n<p>It includes control files for all seven scenarios of the EVAC Impact Assessment Project<\/p>\r\n<p> <\/p>\r\n<p>- Installation guide (how to obtain and install)<\/p>\r\n<p>The package is distributed through the USDOT's JPO Open Source Application Development Portal (OSADP)<\/p>\r\n<p>TRANSIMS software can be downloaded from SourceForge<\/p>\r\n<p> <\/p>\r\n<p>- Other Resources and Links<\/p>\r\n<p>http://sourceforge.net/projects/transims/?source=directory<\/p>",
